OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1778087158
OL,3,CZack Polanski admits he was wrong to
OL,4,Ccall himself a Red Cross spokesperson
OL,6,F"We are investing in strengthening our
OL,7,Fvetting procedures to prevent
OL,8,Finappropriate candidates slipping
OL,9,Fthrough the net."
OL,11,FThe Tory leader, Kemi Badenoch, said
OL,12,Fit called Polanski's judgment into
OL,13,Fquestion.
OL,15,FShe said: "I think that Zack Polanski
OL,16,Fis a man who is in over his head. He
OL,17,Fclearly thinks that politics is just
OL,18,Fsomething fun to do, I don't think
OL,19,Fhe's thought through his views
OL,20,Fparticularly."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/15
